decision_conditions:
CONDITION:   Details and samples of the facing materials shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before any work on the site is commenced. The samples and details shall include:

a)	brickwork (including brick panels with mortar courses) and render;
b)	timber, zinc and resoplan cladding;
c)	roofing materials;
d)	window treatment (including sections and reveals);
e)	balcony and balustrading treatment (including sections);
f)	doors/vents to refuse enclosures and cycle stores;
g)	each entrance to all buildings shown in context and at scale 1:50; and
h)	louvered vents to the Energy Centre. 

The development shall be carried out strictly in accordance with the details so approved, shall be maintained as such thereafter and no change therefrom shall take place without the prior written consent of the Local Planning Authority.

REASON:  To ensure that the Authority may be satisfied with the external appearance of the building.
